Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
init_design_uniquify(25.10)                        init_design_uniquify(25.10)

Name
       init_design_uniquify

Syntax
       init_design_uniquify <value>

       Type: Integer

       Default: 0

       Specifies  whether the top is uniquified. When set to 1 (true), the de-
       sign is uniquified during the read and flatten process. Optimization is
       not allowed on a non-unique design. For use in  a  master/clone  parti-
       tioning  flow,  the value should be 0 (false). The init_design_uniquify
       global variable replaces  the  previous  rda_Input(ui_uniquify_netlist)
       configuration file variable.

Example
              * The  following  command  specifies  that  the design should be
                uniquified automatically after the top cell is flattened.

                set init_design_uniquify {1}

Related Information
              * init_design

